Class GoodController

java.lang.Object
com.example.paragonPioneerBackend.Controller.abstractController.BaseController<Type,Repository,InputDto,Mapper,Service>
com.example.paragonPioneerBackend.Controller.abstractController.SlugableController<Good,GoodRepository,GoodInput,GoodMapper,GoodService>
com.example.paragonPioneerBackend.Controller.GoodController
@Controller @RequestMapping(path="/api/v1/good") public class GoodController extends SlugableController<Good,GoodRepository,GoodInput,GoodMapper,GoodService>
GoodController is a REST controller that handles HTTP requests related to the Good entity. It extends the SlugableController and provides CRUD operations for Good entities. This controller uses the GoodService to interact with the database and perform operations on Good entities. The GoodController class is parameterized with the following types: - Good: The entity type that this controller handles. - GoodRepository: The repository type used for accessing the database. - GoodInput: The DTO type used for creating and updating goods. - GoodMapper: The mapper type used for converting between entities and DTOs. - GoodService: The service type used for business logic operations.
